GREAT PLACE FOR AUTHENTIC SERBIAN FOOD.  I worked at this restaurant for 4 years and I can proudly say that the recipies are authentic and delicious. Once I left this this job, I became a regular customer here. After experiencing discrimination in Serbia for being GAY, I found myself a new home here because my boss and my coworkers were very supportive to me and brought me in as a family member.  I regularly brought in my group of gay friends and they, too, love the quality of food!  We were always treated with great respect and excellent customer service.  We always felt at home here!  I live in Miami now and every time I go to Chicago I make sure to go back along with my friends for  a deliscious meal and amazing time. Simply amazing! Never had Serbian cuisine before and this place blew us away! Meat and bread heavy, (so come hungry) but has other options. Meat is excellent, not spicy, no crazy spices, just an excellent selection of well seasoned & prepared meat! They bake all of their bread daily in house and smoke the meats in house. The platter is definitely enough for 4 people and gives you an amazing selection of all of their meats! Burek takes a bit of time to cook, but is also fantastic. The staff is extremely friendly (we had a long conversation with the owner and chef) and knowledge with their favorites on the menu, especially if you’re looking to try something new. Excellent liquor and cocktail menu as well. You don’t have to pay for quality as quality is part of the experience! Cannot wait to go back and bring all of my friends! A must try and easily new favorite. Thank you 016 & see you very soon!

Excellent! Went here with my wife, mother and her boyfriend on a Saturday night. Not too crowded, but certainly not dead either. We tried the sample platter of grilled meats, feta-stuffed peppers, stuffed cabbage, beef stew and a charcuterie board. While we might have had a meat hangover the next day, we we're all in heaven for the couple of hours we were there. The staff was friendly, gave great suggestions and the chef even brought out our food. This is the kind of neighborhood restaurant we've been looking for. Can't wait to come back again!

Fantastic food. For those will versed in serbian cuisine "Leskovac" grill is held in highest esteem. The cooks and grill masters from this south Serbian  town are known for their near mythological ability to get more flavor into their meats and their secrets have been passed down to the next generation. One of the next generation is Bojan, chef and co-owner of 016(area code of the famed Leskovac town). My third visit now and first time not ordering of the grill menu. Went with a goulash. Traditionally Hungarian dish adopted into Serbian cuisine through it's northern regions. Getting a south Serbian take on it was intriguing and very rewarding. Perfectly cooked and seasoned to perfection - I would absolutely recommend. Now I just have to go back for some Uštipci. Another item I must highlight is the Head cheese or Pihtije in serbian. Best I've had and that's knowing my mother will probably see this. Traditional serbian dish of bone marrow garlic and salt was elevated with delicious tender beef at the bottom and lightened with some citrus notes. Absolutely delightful. On top of everything a welcoming pleasant staff and great service.

It's been a hit and miss in my experiences so far. Burek was good. Meze wasn't as rich as per their photo. I got half as much in my order. Cevapi were rubber like and tasteless. That was a huge disappointment!!! The one thing they've been consistent with is good customer service.

This place brings traditional Leskovac, Serbia specialties to the North Side of Chicago and it's as authentic as it gets. In addition to the food being delicious, the meals are arranged and served as if you are eating at any exclusive $$$ priced downtown joint. Pork sausage that they make in the back is one of the best I've ever tried. 016 Burger can only be better if you are actually within 016 area code in Serbia. Braised veal and Stuffed pork loin are a must try.

EXCELLENT!! Tried the new 016 after it changed from the old and good Kikos. I am a vegetarian of Indian descent married to a Serbian. WOW--we are blown away with the food. We tried: Cherry Peppers - Paprike sa Fetom, Cabbage Salad - Kupus, Fried Peppers - Pohovane Paprike,  Spinach & Cheese Burek, Grilled Meatballs - Leskovački Uštipak, and Pork Stew - Leskovačka Mućkalica. All were simply delicious!! We were blown away by the elegant tast of the Cabbage salad and ordered 2 orders. Each dish was beautifully prepared and served, similar to many high end restaurants in River North/West Loop. Serving sizes are amply and more than enough for one person or perfect to share. Service is quick, constant and everyone was so nice! Kept our water glasses full and provided french fries to our picky toddler.  We were so impressed we booked a table for upcoming Easter celebrations.  Highly recommend for any Serbians and non-Serbs, even if you are vegetarian!!

The food and atmosphere at 016 is excellent. I have eaten at Kiko’s prior to ownership change a few times, and I have nothing bad to say about the food previously, but since 016 took over, I often find myself going out of my way to eat there (other Balkan restaurants are much closer to me). My wife and I go there at least once a month.  The atmosphere is very welcoming. I feel comfortable bringing people there who are not from the Balkans so they can taste our delicious cuisine, and 016 does a great job of plating the dishes they way you would expect of a high end restaurant.  Also, kudos to the bartenders for creating cocktails from rakija (traditional Balkan spirit). I have not found another place in Chicago that does this!  Great job so far! You definitely have a return customer in me.
